      "content": "To achieve a dark crust, aim for a slightly higher oven temperature between 230°C and 250°C to accelerate the Maillard reaction without overcooking the inside. While adding sugar to the water or dough can help, it's often more effective to use a substantial egg yolk wash on the surface before baking, as the additional proteins and fats accelerate browning significantly. You can further fine-tune the crust color by spraying the loaf with water right before baking to increase initial oven spring, which allows for longer time at high heat.",
